===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
''{{w|Shuowen}}'': {{Han compound|力|口|t1=strength|t2=mouth|ls=ic|nocap=1}} — exaggerate; slander. 

Sun Changxu: {{Han compound|力|口|t1=plowing|t2=mouth|ls=ic|nocap=1}} — to put more effort. 口 here indicates exclamations or breath associated with the effort.

===Etymology===
{{och-l|駕|to yoke}} is the [[exopassive]] of {{och-l|加|to add; to attach}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Cognate with {{cog|bo|ཁྲལ||to impose a tax}}, {{cog|my|ကြား|t=between}}.

